cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it deals with computational semantics and word embeddings. It could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) because it uses machine learning techniques to produce the embeddings. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) because it deals with natural language processing and knowledge representation. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category because the paper discusses word similarity evaluations. Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is a less likely but still possible sub-category because the paper mentions the use of neural networks in producing the embeddings.
